# Ingredients
* 2 cups frozen mirepoix, or mixture of carrots, celery, and onion (or shallots) diced
* 4 tsp Penzey's dried garlic, or 4 cloves of garlic diced
* high heat oil, approx 1 tbsp
* 1 cup dried green or red lentils, rinsed
* 1 tbsp hot curry Penzey's powder
* 1 tsp dried thyme
* 1/4 - 1/2 tsp ground fennel seed 
* 1/2 tsp kosher salt
* 1 15 oz can of tomato sauce
* 4 cups of vegetable broth/stock
* 5 cups baby spinach, fresh

* Optional: 
* 1 tsp ground cumin
* sliced chicken, up to 1 lb, in which case add about 1 cup extra stock or water
* sausage sliced, up to 1 lb, in which case add about 1 cup extra stock or water
* chicken broth instead of vegetable broth
* french bread or other artisan bread to serve with soup

# Equipment needed
* pot to heat the stock in
* 6 qt oval Dutch oven and lid
* colander to rinse lentils

#Instructions
* 1. Bring vegetable stock in a pot to boil, then turn down heat to very low
* 2. In Dutch oven, heat oil, then add mirepoix and garlic. 
* 3. Saute for about 5 minutes if frozen, less time if using fresh vegetables.
* 3a. If making with chicken and/or sausage, add at this point and saute until cooked.
* 4. Add curry powder, thyme, ground fennel seed, salt, and cumin if using.
* 5. Stir and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute.
* 6. Stir in lentils, tomato sauce, and broth.
* 7. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to high simmer, cover, and cook for 15-20 minutes.
* 8. Test lentil; when cooked, thoroughly stir in the spinach and turn off the heat. 
* Serve with fresh bread.
